SDR
===

I/Q data: http://www.ni.com/tutorial/4805/en/ 

Crystal Radio
=============

Day 1 - A 45 min intro to basic radio theory. Maybe with some Marconi et al thrown in.
Need to cover RF spectrum, modulation, antennas, atmospherics etc.
Possible crystal set demo.

Day 2 - build a working crystal set.


WSPR radio
==========

Day 1- Explain Weak Signals with a light dusting of radio theory.
Demo of running WSPR software on linux.

Day 2 -  build and use a WSPR receiver.


ADSB
====

Day 1 - Long intro to and demo of ADSB
Day 2 - make an ADSB antenna and find planes


FM Radio
========

Day 1 - Radio theory with a focus on FM and all its enhancements (like RDS)
Day 2 - Either build an FM Rx or decode stuff with a dongle and software

Regen receivers
===============

Day 1 - Olde fashioned radio (AM or SSB) can be received several ways.
Superhet has its followers.
Regen is an option.
Demo regen.

Day 2 - Build and test a regen receiver.

Solar Powered ADSB station
==========================

How to run a Raspberry Pi from a battery and a panel
What does a decent antenna look like
Getting your data online and useful
Nice software setup (dump1090 forks)

